Description: Fragment of oval handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium, light brown; mixed inclusions. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 181, 13 or 184, 4 (the former illustrated here). A parallel in the Benaki collection, Alexandria Museum, is probably from the same die. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1558)
